<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" author="Brandon Kiem" dateTime="2021-06-21T16:14:09" id="_44c436f6-9e73-41b6-b331-4251d92eca4e" outputclass="ncc-clause" type="insert"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>J3D13</sptc><title id="_9cb5a4d8-db0f-4c0b-95dd-ea6a701bb8a2">Shading of a sole-occupancy unit of a Class 2 building or a Class 4 part of a building</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><clause-variation deleted-text="J3D13 does not apply in NSW." variation="NSW" variation-type="DELETE">NSW DELETE Clause</clause-variation><subclause id="_d8c0c630-a85f-4165-9b7b-e1f9b7e55127" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_7cc9ec59-56d6-4b68-9a2b-d417cc4499f4">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Where shading is <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1432_4.0.0.xml#_a5b45a91-1ac3-44a8-8644-acfc09c225a9" id="_30edc9e2-c64b-433e-87b7-56c47826461a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">required</xref> to comply with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/6317_0.48.0.xml#_14eb980f-66ee-40e8-bf62-04951dfd47e1" id="_1eb70bdb-55ff-4b29-b722-d3b6b5895706" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">J3D11</xref> or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/6356_0.53.0.xml#_4f200a04-174f-400f-9b83-6aba3affe836" id="_da7a30aa-315c-4690-af6b-7397a65ff3bf" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">J3D12</xref>, it must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_88d8b202-be44-4d2b-ac80-ab8ad452c500">be provided by an external permanent projection, such as a verandah, balcony, fixed canopy, eaves, shading hood or carport, which—<ol><li id="_d596c36c-f428-4f87-bd34-70ea11a5b3e2">extends horizontally on both sides of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1319_2.9.0.xml#_9067b5ce-fa3e-4afd-9b3a-b3520543cb5d" id="_3765a2a8-4fbe-4301-870f-71fdcf40b0e4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">glazing</xref> for a distance greater than or equal to the projection distance P in <xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-23T11:40:00" xt:id="5e948787-f4ec-4401-9377-88ba748f673f"/><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/530_0.8.0.xml#_4c5c6f74-f15b-42a4-a618-3a85ca80c889" id="_e1ca414d-7eaa-4b34-a02c-66860f5e5a18" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure S37C7a</xref><xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="5e948787-f4ec-4401-9377-88ba748f673f"/><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-04-23T11:39:00" xt:id="87715a90-b6d5-4a50-8440-d0170e0b5b53"/><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/530_0.8.0.xml#_4c5c6f74-f15b-42a4-a618-3a85ca80c889" id="_33ffbf64-a738-438f-b8f2-e7c3f658ff31" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure S37C7</xref><xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="87715a90-b6d5-4a50-8440-d0170e0b5b53"/>; or</li><li>provide the equivalent shading to (i) with a reveal or the like; or</li></ol></li><li id="_acf89af3-16f5-460d-9521-74db0149fa69">be provided by an external shading device, such as a shutter, blind, vertical or horizontal building screen with blades, battens or slats, which—<ol><li id="_b82775a4-c912-4fa4-b316-fe5dbd34673b">is capable of restricting at least 80% of the summer solar radiation; and</li><li>if adjustable, is readily operated either manually, mechanically or electronically by the building occupants.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause></clause>